30/09/2007
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Macedonian citizen Irfan Sulejmani and three of his co-workers from the International Committee of the Red Cross were released on Saturday (September 29th), after three days of captivity in Afghanistan. 
The four men are in good health and said they were treated well by their abductors. 
A Taliban commander told the AP that he ordered the kidnapping because he thought they were spies, but decided to let them go after it was proved they were Red Cross employees. 
The four men were in Afghanistan's Wardak province to help win the release of a German hostage. 
(AP, Makfax, AFP, A1, Dnevnik - 29/09/07)
